    "abstract": [
        {
            "text": "Search for light-speed anisotropies using Compton scattering of high-energy electrons D. Rebreyend on behalf of the experimental team *",
            "paragraph_rank": 0,
            "section_rank": 1
        }
    ],
    "body_text": [
        {
            "text": "Experimental searches for anisotropies in c and, more generally, for Lorentz violating (LV) processes are currently motivated by theoretical studies in the context of quantum gravity. ",
            "paragraph_rank": 1,
            "section_rank": 2
        },
        {
            "text": "Recent approaches to Planckscale physics can indeed accommodate minuscule violations of Lorentz symmetry. ",
            "paragraph_rank": 1,
            "section_rank": 2
        },
        {
            "text": "1 The present result is based on a laboratory experiment using only photons and electrons in an environment where gravity is negligible. ",
            "paragraph_rank": 1,
            "section_rank": 2,
            "ref_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 0,
                    "end": 1,
                    "type": "bibr",
                    "ref_id": "b0",
                    "text": "1"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "text": "Lorentz violation can then be described by the single-flavor QED limit of the flatspacetime mSME. ",
            "paragraph_rank": 1,
            "section_rank": 2
        },
        {
            "text": "2,5 In this framework, photons have a modified dispersion relation:",
            "paragraph_rank": 1,
            "section_rank": 2,
            "ref_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 0,
                    "end": 2,
                    "type": "bibr",
                    "ref_id": "b7",
                    "text": "2,"
                },
                {
                    "start": 2,
                    "end": 3,
                    "type": "bibr",
                    "ref_id": "b15",
                    "text": "5"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "text": "Here, \u03bb \u00b5 = (\u03c9, \u03bb\u03bb) denotes the photon 4-momentum and\u03bb is a unit 3vector. ",
            "paragraph_rank": 2,
            "section_rank": 2
        },
        {
            "text": "The space-time constant mSME \u03ba vector specifies a preferred direction in the Universe which violates Lorentz symmetry, and can be interpreted as generating a direction-dependent refractive index of the vacuum",
            "paragraph_rank": 2,
            "section_rank": 2,
            "entity_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 77,
                    "end": 85,
                    "type": "software",
                    "rawForm": "Universe",
                    "resp": "whitelist",
                    "id": "software-simple-w0"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "text": "The basic experimental idea is that in a terrestrial laboratory the photon 3-momentum in a Compton-scattering process changes direction due to the Earth's rotation. ",
            "paragraph_rank": 3,
            "section_rank": 2,
            "entity_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 91,
                    "end": 98,
                    "type": "software",
                    "rawForm": "Compton",
                    "resp": "whitelist",
                    "id": "software-simple-w1"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "text": "The photons are thus affected by the anisotropies in Eq. ",
            "paragraph_rank": 3,
            "section_rank": 2
        },
        {
            "text": "1leading to sidereal effects in the kinematics of the process.",
            "paragraph_rank": 3,
            "section_rank": 2,
            "ref_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 0,
                    "end": 1,
                    "ref_id": "formula_0",
                    "text": "1"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "text": "The experimental set-up at GRAAL involves counter-propagating incoming electrons and photons with 3-momenta p = pp and \u03bb = \u2212\u03bbp, respectively. ",
            "paragraph_rank": 4,
            "section_rank": 2
        },
        {
            "text": "The conventional Compton edge (CE) then occurs for outgoing photons that are backscattered at 180 \u2022 , so that the kinematics is essentially one dimensional along the beam directionp. ",
            "paragraph_rank": 4,
            "section_rank": 2,
            "entity_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 17,
                    "end": 24,
                    "type": "software",
                    "rawForm": "Compton",
                    "resp": "whitelist",
                    "id": "software-simple-w2"
                },
                {
                    "start": 31,
                    "end": 33,
                    "type": "software",
                    "rawForm": "CE",
                    "resp": "whitelist",
                    "id": "software-simple-w3"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "text": "Energy conservation for this process reads",
            "paragraph_rank": 4,
            "section_rank": 2
        },
        {
            "text": "where \u03bb \u2032 = \u03bb \u2032p is the 3-momentum of the CE photon, and 3-momentum conservation has been implemented. ",
            "paragraph_rank": 5,
            "section_rank": 2,
            "entity_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 42,
                    "end": 44,
                    "type": "software",
                    "rawForm": "CE",
                    "resp": "whitelist",
                    "id": "software-simple-w4"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "text": "At leading order, the physical solution of Eq. ",
            "paragraph_rank": 5,
            "section_rank": 2
        },
        {
            "text": "2is",
            "paragraph_rank": 5,
            "section_rank": 2,
            "ref_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 0,
                    "end": 1,
                    "ref_id": "formula_2",
                    "text": "2"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "text": "Here,",
            "paragraph_rank": 6,
            "section_rank": 2
        },
        {
            "text": "1+4 \u03b3 \u03bb / m denotes the conventional value of the CE energy. ",
            "paragraph_rank": 7,
            "section_rank": 2,
            "entity_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 50,
                    "end": 52,
                    "type": "software",
                    "rawForm": "CE",
                    "resp": "whitelist",
                    "id": "software-simple-w5"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "text": "Given the actual experimental data of m = 511 keV, p = 6030 MeV, and \u03bb = 3.5 eV, yields \u03b3 \u2243 p/m = 11800 and \u03bb CE = 1473 MeV. ",
            "paragraph_rank": 7,
            "section_rank": 2,
            "entity_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 60,
                    "end": 63,
                    "type": "software",
                    "rawForm": "MeV",
                    "resp": "whitelist",
                    "id": "software-simple-w6"
                },
                {
                    "start": 110,
                    "end": 112,
                    "type": "software",
                    "rawForm": "CE",
                    "resp": "whitelist",
                    "id": "software-simple-w7"
                },
                {
                    "start": 120,
                    "end": 123,
                    "type": "software",
                    "rawForm": "MeV",
                    "resp": "whitelist",
                    "id": "software-simple-w8"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "text": "The numerical value of the factor in front of \u03ba \u2022p is about 1.6 \u00d7 10 8 . ",
            "paragraph_rank": 7,
            "section_rank": 2
        },
        {
            "text": "It is this large amplification factor (essentially given by \u03b3 2 ) that yields the exceptional sensitivity of the CE to\u03ba o+ .",
            "paragraph_rank": 7,
            "section_rank": 2,
            "entity_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 113,
                    "end": 115,
                    "type": "software",
                    "rawForm": "CE",
                    "resp": "whitelist",
                    "id": "software-simple-w9"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "text": "Expressed in the Sun-centered inertial frame (X, Y, Z) 4 and taking into account GRAAL's latitude and beam direction, eq. ",
            "paragraph_rank": 8,
            "section_rank": 2,
            "ref_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 55,
                    "end": 56,
                    "type": "bibr",
                    "ref_id": "b14",
                    "text": "4"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "text": "3becomes",
            "paragraph_rank": 8,
            "section_rank": 2,
            "ref_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 0,
                    "end": 1,
                    "ref_id": "formula_3",
                    "text": "3"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "text": "Incoming photons overlap with the ESRF beam over a 6.5 m long straight section. ",
            "paragraph_rank": 9,
            "section_rank": 2
        },
        {
            "text": "Due to their energy loss, scattered electrons are extracted from the main beam in the magnetic dipole following the straight section. ",
            "paragraph_rank": 9,
            "section_rank": 2
        },
        {
            "text": "Their position can then be accurately measured in the so-called tagging system located 50 cm after the exit of the dipole. ",
            "paragraph_rank": 9,
            "section_rank": 2
        },
        {
            "text": "This system is composed of a position-sensitive Si \u00b5-strip detector (128 strips of 300 \u00b5m pitch, 500 \u00b5m thick) associated to a set of fast plastic scintillators. ",
            "paragraph_rank": 9,
            "section_rank": 2
        },
        {
            "text": "A typical Si \u00b5-strip count spectrum near the CE is shown in Fig. 1 for the multiline UV mode (364, 351, 333 nm) of the laser used in this measurement. ",
            "paragraph_rank": 9,
            "section_rank": 2,
            "ref_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 60,
                    "end": 66,
                    "type": "figure",
                    "ref_id": "fig_0",
                    "text": "Fig. 1"
                }
            ],
            "entity_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 45,
                    "end": 47,
                    "type": "software",
                    "rawForm": "CE",
                    "resp": "whitelist",
                    "id": "software-simple-w10"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "text": "The fitting function, also plotted, is based on the sum of 3 error functions plus background and includes 6 free parameters. ",
            "paragraph_rank": 9,
            "section_rank": 2
        },
        {
            "text": "The CE position (location of the central line), x CE , can be measured with an excellent resolution of \u223c 3 \u00b5m. ",
            "paragraph_rank": 9,
            "section_rank": 2,
            "entity_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 4,
                    "end": 6,
                    "type": "software",
                    "rawForm": "CE",
                    "resp": "whitelist",
                    "id": "software-simple-w11"
                },
                {
                    "start": 50,
                    "end": 52,
                    "type": "software",
                    "rawForm": "CE",
                    "resp": "whitelist",
                    "id": "software-simple-w12"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "text": "A sample of the time series of the CE positions relative to the ESRF beam covering 24 h is displayed in Fig. 2c, along with the tagging-box temperature ( Fig. 2b) and the ESRF beam intensity (Fig. 2a). ",
            "paragraph_rank": 9,
            "section_rank": 2,
            "ref_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 104,
                    "end": 111,
                    "type": "figure",
                    "ref_id": "fig_1",
                    "text": "Fig. 2c"
                },
                {
                    "start": 154,
                    "end": 161,
                    "type": "figure",
                    "ref_id": "fig_1",
                    "text": "Fig. 2b"
                },
                {
                    "start": 191,
                    "end": 200,
                    "type": "figure",
                    "ref_id": "fig_1",
                    "text": "(Fig. 2a)"
                }
            ],
            "entity_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 35,
                    "end": 37,
                    "type": "software",
                    "rawForm": "CE",
                    "resp": "whitelist",
                    "id": "software-simple-w13"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "text": "The sharp steps present in Fig. 2a correspond to the twice-a-day refills of the ESRF ring. ",
            "paragraph_rank": 9,
            "section_rank": 2,
            "ref_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 27,
                    "end": 34,
                    "type": "figure",
                    "ref_id": "fig_1",
                    "text": "Fig. 2a"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "text": "The similarity of the temperature and CE spectra combined with their correlation with the ESRF beam intensity led us to interpret the continuous and slow drift of the CE positions as a result of the tagging-box dilation induced by the x-ray heat load.",
            "paragraph_rank": 9,
            "section_rank": 2,
            "entity_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 38,
                    "end": 40,
                    "type": "software",
                    "rawForm": "CE",
                    "resp": "whitelist",
                    "id": "software-simple-w14"
                },
                {
                    "start": 167,
                    "end": 169,
                    "type": "software",
                    "rawForm": "CE",
                    "resp": "whitelist",
                    "id": "software-simple-w15"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "text": "To get rid of this trivial time dependence, raw data have been fitted with the sum of two exponential whose time constants have been extracted from the time evolution of the temperature data. ",
            "paragraph_rank": 10,
            "section_rank": 2
        },
        {
            "text": "The corrected and final spectrum is obtained by subtraction of the fitted function from the raw data, (Fig. 2d).",
            "paragraph_rank": 10,
            "section_rank": 2,
            "ref_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 102,
                    "end": 111,
                    "type": "figure",
                    "ref_id": "fig_1",
                    "text": "(Fig. 2d)"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "text": "The usual equation for the deflection of charges in a magnetic field together with momentum conservation in Compton scattering determines the relation between the CE variations \u2206xCE",
            "paragraph_rank": 11,
            "section_rank": 2,
            "entity_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 108,
                    "end": 115,
                    "type": "software",
                    "rawForm": "Compton",
                    "resp": "whitelist",
                    "id": "software-simple-w16"
                },
                {
                    "start": 163,
                    "end": 165,
                    "type": "software",
                    "rawForm": "CE",
                    "resp": "whitelist",
                    "id": "software-simple-w17"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "text": "xCE and a hypothetical CE photon 3-momentum oscillation \u2206\u03bb \u2032 \u03bb \u2032 :",
            "paragraph_rank": 12,
            "section_rank": 2,
            "entity_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 23,
                    "end": 25,
                    "type": "software",
                    "rawForm": "CE",
                    "resp": "whitelist",
                    "id": "software-simple-w18"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "text": "To search for a modulation, 14765 data points collected in about 1 week of data taking have been folded modulo a sidereal day (Fig. 3). ",
            "paragraph_rank": 13,
            "section_rank": 2,
            "ref_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 126,
                    "end": 134,
                    "type": "figure",
                    "text": "(Fig. 3)"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "text": "The error bars are purely statistical and the histogram is in agreement with a null signal (\u03c7 2 = 1.04). ",
            "paragraph_rank": 13,
            "section_rank": 2
        },
        {
            "text": "To look for a harmonic oscillation (A sin(\u2126t + \u03c6)), we have performed a statistical analysis based on the Bayesian approach. ",
            "paragraph_rank": 13,
            "section_rank": 2
        },
        {
            "text": "The resulting upper bound is A < 2.5 \u00d7 10 \u22126 at 95% CL.",
            "paragraph_rank": 13,
            "section_rank": 2,
            "entity_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 52,
                    "end": 54,
                    "type": "software",
                    "rawForm": "CL",
                    "resp": "whitelist",
                    "id": "software-simple-w19"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "text": "We next consider effects that could conceal an actual sidereal signal. ",
            "paragraph_rank": 14,
            "section_rank": 2
        },
        {
            "text": "Besides a direct oscillation of the orbit, the two quantities that may affect the result are the dipole magnetic field and the momentum of the ESRF beam p. ",
            "paragraph_rank": 14,
            "section_rank": 2
        },
        {
            "text": "All these parameters are linked to the machine operation, and their stability follows directly from the accelerator performance. ",
            "paragraph_rank": 14,
            "section_rank": 2
        },
        {
            "text": "A detailed analysis of the ESRF database allows us to conclude that a sidereal oscillation of 6 12 18 t (hr)",
            "paragraph_rank": 14,
            "section_rank": 2,
            "ref_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 94,
                    "end": 95,
                    "type": "bibr",
                    "ref_id": "b18",
                    "text": "6"
                }
