        {
            "text": "Full set of data folded modulo a sidereal day (24 bins). ",
            "paragraph_rank": 15,
            "section_rank": 2
        },
        {
            "text": "The error bars are purely statistical and agree with the dispersion of the data points (\u03c7 2 = 1.04 for the unbinned histogram). ",
            "paragraph_rank": 15,
            "section_rank": 2
        },
        {
            "text": "The shaded area corresponds to the region of non-excluded signal amplitudes.",
            "paragraph_rank": 15,
            "section_rank": 2
        },
        {
            "text": "any of these parameters cannot exceed a few parts in 10 7 and is negligible.",
            "paragraph_rank": 16,
            "section_rank": 2
        },
        {
            "text": "We can now conclude that our upper bound on a hypothetical sidereal oscillation of the CE energy is: \u2206\u03bb \u2032 /\u03bb \u2032 < 2.5 \u00d7 10 \u22126 (95 % CL) ,",
            "paragraph_rank": 17,
